3.Given an unsorted array arr[] of integers and a key which is present in this array. Find the start index (index where the element is first found from left in the array) and end index (index where the element is first found from right in the array). Return an array of length 2 with elements start index and end index.
Platform: GeeksforGeeks 
SOURCECODE : class Solution {
    public ArrayList<Integer> findIndex(int[] arr, int key) {
      int a=-1,b=-1;
        int n=arr.length;
        ArrayList<Integer> l=new ArrayList<>();
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(arr[i]==key){
              if(a==-1){
                a=i;}
              b=i;  
          }  } 
         l.add(a);
        l.add(b);
        return l;
    }
}
